```

### Form Accessibility
- Every input must have explicit `<label for="id">` or wrapper
- Never rely on placeholder-only labeling
- Required fields indicated with aria-required
- Error messages linked with aria-describedby

### Motion & Animation
- **Respect `prefers-reduced-motion: reduce`**
- Provide static alternatives for all animations
- GameCube boot sequence must be skippable
- Petal effects disabled for reduced motion users

### Interactive Elements
- Minimum 44px touch targets for mobile
- Clear focus states for all interactive elements
- Descriptive link text (avoid "click here")
- Proper semantic HTML (buttons vs links vs divs)

### ARIA Implementation
- Use semantic HTML first, ARIA second
- Proper roles: `role="img"` for decorative SVGs
- Live regions for dynamic content updates
- Modal accessibility with focus trapping

### Testing Standards
- Run axe-core accessibility checks
- Test with screen readers (NVDA/JAWS)
- Verify keyboard-only navigation
- Test with 200% browser zoom